## Import

Use the `user_name` to import a user. For example

```sh
 $ pulumi import aws:memorydb/user:User example my-user
```

 The `passwords` are not available for imported resources, as this information cannot be read back from the MemoryDB API.

## Supporting Types

{{% choosable language csharp %}}

            title="Required">

</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">List&lt;string&gt;</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}The set of passwords used for authentication. You can create up to two passwords for each user.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-required"
            title="Required">
        <span id="type_csharp">
<a href="#type_csharp" style="color: inherit; text-decoration: inherit;">Type</a>
</span>
        <span class="property-indicator"></span>
        <span class="property-type">string</span>
    </dt>
    <dd>{{% md %}}Indicates whether the user requires a password to authenticate. Must be set to `password`.
{{% /md %}}</dd><dt class="property-optional"
            title="Optional">
